content: Very useful app. It gives suggestions for any type of activities that you would like to do while you're at your vacation destination. I used it for a trip to Vegas. There were great suggestions for shows, dining and attractions. I found a very useful and will definitely be using it again for any other types of trips and even for activities in my home city.

This is the BEST app EVER! I NEVER plan a trip without it! Gives all the options to do in an area, restaruants, hotels. It has it ALL. Along with reviews so you can decide if you want to include it on your trip. I have crossed a few things off our list based on the terrible reviews. I am glad to have not wasted that money and have the opportunity to select something else as time is so precious on vacation.

I love it. works great.. gives you great tips on travel. photos.. and I've booked many many trips on this app. saves a lot of time. I've tried looking at other flights to see if i could get a better price. sometimes I found cheaper just by a few dollars.. but was more hassle. here a one stop shop. !! highly recommend this app!

TripAdvisor is my mobile pocket guide for every city in the world, and plenty of out-of-the way destinations too. I have had success booking hotels through the app, making reservations, and always finding a few options to add to my sightseeing to-do list. I trust these reviews because nobody is forced, or rewarded, for leaving them.

I like the app itself, but I don't want DAILY emails spamming up my inbox! I've repeatedly tried to "unsubscribe" in my account settings but it won't allow me to save the settings so I'm still getting the daily emails. It's sad when they think have to shove something down your throat every single day! I will be deleting my account altogether & blocking the email address! EDIT:May 16, 2019 WOW! I'm impressed! TripAdvisor has changed so much for the better since the last time I used it! Thanks!

I always check trip advisor when traveling to find a place to stay or eat, and find the reviews very helpful. One suggestion that would be very helpful for those of us traveling with pets (would probably help with small children too): indicate if the place has a private entrance. I always have to scroll through all the pictures and hope I can find one that shows them. Updates have made it difficult navigate:. loved ability to search my reviews but no longer able to sort by location.

I use TripAdvisor all the time! I love how I can save a trip I'm planning and add to it, change it or delete it whenever I want! I love all the answers I get from different destinations that help me make my travel plans. I think what I love be the most is seeing everyone else's reviews of places, hotels/motels, restraints, businesses, just all sorts of reviews that help in my trip decision making. Especially having young kids!!! I don't go anywhere without checking reviews to see if it will work

I have been using TripAdvisor for several years to plan trips in the United States and internationally. It has always been one of my top resources The recent update is a disappointment. Previously, you could organize activities within a trip by date. You can no longer do that and can no longer change the order of saved activities within a trip. This was a helpful tool when planning trip days chronologically. Please bring this feature back!

Great travel app. Love being able to easily find information. Appreciate unbiased reviews from other travelers. Keep up the good work. UPDATE: My review was originally posted in 2016. Three years later I'm still using and loving this app. One of the best things about it - if I end up on TripAdvisor in my browser and it's running kind of slow with lots of open tabs, I simply move over to the app and everything moves lightning fast. Excellent!

This is my go-to app when it comes to trying out new restaurants and places to see. I can almost always fully rely on the ratings and what's said about a place. I'm a bit of a perfectionist, especially when it comes to Italian food. A 3.2 Italian restaurant for me might be a 4.8 for 200 other people. For other cuisines, however, I've generally found Tripadvisor to be spot on. I've also used this app to book a hotel when I needed one quickly, and Trip Advisor will find you the best prices.

It is really good. I really liked the museums that have guns (one example is the Rockford Island Arsenal Museum in Illinois, Chicago). I also liked the historical museums that also have historical guns (one example is the Louisiana Military Museum in Ruston, Louisiana). The thing is when I look up gun museums and historical gun musums (like the examples that I just mentioned), the results get a little mixed up. I want to look up gun museums nearby or worldwide. that is what I wanted. Thank you!

always helpful. I enjoy giving reviews too, and then another other Travelers can know about the gems that are along the roadways and hidden in the towns we all zip past too quickly. and there are a few stinkers that I have encountered. it's good to be able to warn others about things that might go wrong on their trip. No one wants to try to check in hotel after hours on the road, and find out nobody's there to let you in. Overall It's a wonderful tool. I really enjoyed sharing my photos too.

Aw man! What can I say about this app? The TripAdvisor app is the most amazing travel and hotel booking app! You can do everything with it! Book flights! Book hotel rooms! It shows you the lowest price and compares it to other prices for whatever you may be booking, whether it be a flight or a hotel room! I absolutely love it! Best travel app I've ever seen or ever used! I will definitely be using TripAdvisor for all of my travel plans and needs!

A trusted Travel App. When I'm planning a trip the first thing I do is go to Trip Advisor. I use "Plan", and save it. I organize my tripby name and save, Places to See, hotels, and restaurants . You can add notes too. I read and trust the reviews, it has never disappointed me. I also review the places I've saved to help other travelers. Trip Advisor let's you save your Planned trip so I can go back years to see the places I've been to.

This is my go to app anytime i go into a less familiar area. It is very easy to use and works flawlessly. My only additional recc for a user is dont get caught up in the ranking for hotels and restaurants. Sometime the top ranked ones are not the best fit. There are some treasures that are ranked lower. Be willing to look further down the ranks for both hotels and restaurants as well as read some comments.

I really enjoy TripAdvisor. I use it for day trips, weekend getaways, and vacations. There are reviews by other travelers and you can ask questions about your destination. You can book your trip through the app. It's very convenient and easy to use. Plan spur of the moment trips and getaways or do advanced planning for a trip in the future. You can save places to favorites, ex. I have a trip with saved places for our anniversary getaway, and I'm saving places for a planned trip to Iceland.

I've grown to refer to Trip Advisor in one way or another for ALL of my trips. The traveler's photos and reviews are always helpful. I, myself, contribute reviews and photos, so I have more trust in the review and can get a "truer" gauge of the place. I love being able to save places in a file during my research and planning. Great app!

I use TA my personal travel agent, with me still being in charge of my trips. I love that you can save favorites, helps keeping places and restaurants I'm interested flagged. I also appreciate that details of hotels and many options, before picking the hotel and type of room. i have never been disappointed in my choices of hotels, restaurants and things to do. Thanks toTA actually felt confident to book our whole trip by myself. That was huge for me especially in a foreign country. T

I started using Trip Advisor on a business trip to find a place to eat. I know use it as a way to share my experiences with others. My family and I love to eat, especially at locally owned restaurants, so now others can learn from our experiences. Years later this is still "my go to app" when planning a trip or looking for new places to explorer.

Changing my review due to app updates. The app functions much better now! Original review: I love trip advisor but I've never had more problems with an application and the website always tries to switch me over to the app. This would be a 5 star rating if this app didn't have so many bugs. Occasionally while viewing places if I hit back, instead of going to the list it just cancels out. These are two of a variety of issues this app has. This is honestly my worst worst functiong application.

Yay! After noticing this recent app overhaul since last reviewing back in July '19, the single feature I use the most (and probably the most popular among millions of users) has returned: day-by-day trip itineraries! Finally able to plan each of day of your trip again. A feature so simple yet the only reason I and many others returned to TripAdvisor time and time again. Thanks so much for bringing this feature back! Keep up the good work!

First app I go to whenever we travel. I really appreciate Trip Advisor's results when I am searching for specifics or looking for ideas. The reviews posted by everyone are really helpful. It is great to be able ask questions of people who have 'been there, done that. The ratings given by T.A. are also helpful. Lots of great helpful information! Keep up the great work!

I always refer to TripAdvisor for my travel needs. I have been able to get ideas, read reviews, roughly plan my budget all in one place. The reviews both good and bad are always helpful. Having a heads up on what to embrace or avoid from the country forums is usually right on point. I am still using TripAdvisor to plan my trips, tours, restaurants. I am very appreciative of the opinions of others. I have referred many people to TripAdvisor as they try to plan their own trips. I ❤ TripAdvisor!

Awesome recommendations; Trip Advisor is the online connection to the 'What, Where & When' Hotels, Air Travel, places to eat, best tours, public transportation ideas, the must do's, the best prices. It's so easy to personalize to ur location, interests & needs. *Q&A a bonus because it's verified thru other travelers. ☆ Good luck & enjoy

20170619: Instead of seeing other's reviews of places I am searching, I see mine. This is truly annoying. Also, the filters for different types of places, i.e. romantic, family friendly, exotic, et cetera no longer appear. This makes TripAdvisor less useful. Getting odd results. As I search for results for one locale, I am being provided the results from elsewhere, and the app cycles through multiple locations unprompted.

I love Trip Advisor. I use it for every vacation. It's better than Google reviews because people who post reviews really take time to give an accurate picture of their experience. Plus, TripAdvisor ranks things for each city which is helpful when trying to figure out how to spend our time.

I like trip advisor because I can compare prices on hotels over many booking sites all on one place. The user reviews are helpful and usually very detailed. This also applies to reviews of restaurants, landmarks, and just about anywhere else you can visit while on a trip. I always use it to get an idea of where I would like to stay, eat and visit while planning a week long vacation or a quick getaway.

Very simple and easy to use it also transforms on to your laptop or your desktop with the same information. I like using the form and asking other Travelers questions to get information and confirmation of activities. Still pretty good information for adults, and it lists things to do as well as restaurants and hotels

Very good app! If you're planning a trip or even looking for local options, you need this app. It's definitely one of my most used apps for a reason. It's very informative and helpful. It allows you to save things you find at a location to your "places" list that you create so when you go, open your saved destination and have at it. I planned a weeklong Vegas trip of things to do, places to eat, etc this way and never missed a thing. I ran out of vacation before I did options! Highly recommended

I rely on TripAdvisor almost exclusively when I travel out of town. I have been in 48(ND, AK) of our 50 states and for the most part, the restaurants have seemed worthy of their ranking with very few exceptions. I used your app in London, Paris, Switzerland, Venice & Rome and it ensured my family that we would eat at a restaurant that was great not just in a great location.

Absolutely love the TripAdvisor App. With one simple touch I have access to tons of reviews which I rely on when I plan my vacations. My only hiccup and I'm sure it's me, is that for some reason I haven't figure out how to see the traveler's photos from new to old. But other than that I use the App all the time. Definitely recommend downloading it to your phone.

Ive used TripAdvisor to both complain and give praise. As well as a resource for finding things and getting an understanding of those places worth BEFORE spending my time and money. TripAdvisor should start paying me however... im growing weary of this all being 1 sided. Although TripAdvisor is a valuable resource... there are several competing resources. TripAdvisor should do something for people who have taken the time to write hundreds of views and snap/upload hundreds of pictures.

Been a trip advisor for many years, and I appreciate the input from all other advisors and have been a continual reviewer the entire time. Five stars ☆☆☆☆☆ I continue to use Trip Advisor, as I feel they give all the people using the app the best most up to date information to make informed decisions in all areas of travel, with real time accuracy. Travel Advisors do what they do because they, like myself and all who use this app benefit from a passion to explore and report all that we see ..

They have concise and best information available for almost all places. Comments and photos shared by users is very helpful. TripAdvisor has their own ranking/certification of places. I generally avoid booking tours - instead relying on self guided trips, however the few tours I have done through TripAdvisor have been pretty good. So I would recommend that as well

I travel all over the US for work. I often find myself alone in a new city wondering where to eat lunch and dinner. This is my go to app for finding a new restaurant. I'll sometimes use other apps, but for finding a good retaurant TripAdvisor is in my opinion the best. I also use this app to check out and select my hotels in advance. A great app to the road warrior.

Informative! It really is the "Go To" app when traveling in Central America. Everyone uses it, businesses depend on it and travelers share their opinion and advice. It's been an awesome resource. I've booked our excursions, our flights, found a few restaurants. We even needed to find a taxi driver who spoke English for a 6am pick up in Panama. Found a local who did it (because Taxis don't start until 7:30am). Without finding him, we would have missed our bus to Costa Rica!

Have been using this website for almost 10 years now and have seen it grow in sophistication & provide a wealth of info on tourist places. Love it & would make sure to look at it whether dining or visiting or trying to find Things to do. Great site. It's been 7 years since I posted the previous para and it has grown more sophisticated and useful as time has passed.

My wife and I use this app all the time when we travel. There is nothing as boring as traveling and going to chain/cookie cutter restaurants. We have found so many excellent restaurants as well as different things to do because of using this app. Also a BIG shout out to all the people who 5ake the time to write reviews. They are especially helpful.

Really helpful tool for planning a trip. In addition to being able to read honest traveler reviews, love the ability to save specific attractions and locals in a specific place. Easy to hit on the attraction and the get pretty accurate directions using Google Maps. If you are an Independent traveler who likes to plan your own unique trips, this is a must!

I love Trip Advisor! I use it for all my long trips as well as for a weekend getaway. So helpful in areas of finding accomadations, foood, things to do, etc. The reviews are invaluable and I depend on them greatly in making my final decisions along with the information in the forums and questions and answers. Trip Advisor is a great travel app!!

If I'm away or at home, TripAdvisor is my go to app for things to do or places to eat. You can make TripAdvisor your one stop for all your travel needs and be happy about it. We are the ones leaving the the ratings and experiences for others to decide what's good for them... ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

I love the new updates that the app has made! The "trips" category and being able to create and save to something organized is really helpful when planning a trip and keeping all your information in one place. The only thing I'd still love to see added to the app is a place on your personal account where you can visibly see how many people have read each of your reviews, as well as the monthly update of how many overall readers you have. Thanks, TripAdvisor!

Always Informative... This is my go-to app when I want to look at restaurants or things to do... I think that trip advisor is a great tool... I always feel that the reviews are by honest travelers like myself who speak openly and candidly about their experiences and I always find their reviews of restaurants and hotels very helpful and planning my trips...

I've used numerous times with wonderful results. When cancellation is required, it's very easy to ensure refunds. The payment protection in place to ensure ease for everyone. I've booked on other sites before and have had major issues with the availability of dates changing after booking. Getting refunded when the location made the changes, I did not. The reviews ate also very helpful.

Thanks to all the reviewers, the reviews are really helpful when traveling to unknown places. This is my go to when validating destinations for most travel; it adds a lot of great options by opening doors to new places and experiences. My favorite feature is the "search this area" on the map for restaurants and hotels. Accurate and easy to use.

Last year I went to India and I used tripadvisor to plan everything but my flight. Tour guides, restaurants, places I wanted to see , even advice on transportation. I went by myself. I have never ever traveled anywhere by myself but I had done enough research on TripAdvisor to feel confidant about going alone. I don't know where or when I will be traveling internationally again but I will count on TripAdvisor to help me plan my trip.

Provides Exceptional Advice! Whenever we are on a trip, we check Trip Advisor for suggestions regarding restaurants and hotels. We also take heed to people's reviews about certain attractions. Most importantly, Trip Advisor allows any and all opinions, not just all positive or all negative. We sometimes weigh people's words with a grain of salt, but usually the advice is solid!

App runs well. The information on TripAdvisor has helped us plan everything from meals to hotel rooms on our trips abroad. I find that the restaurant filter is much better than Google, as it allows you to find restaurants that fall within specific budgets lines not only filtering by ratings.

I love this app because when a restaurant's really really good I love ❤️ to tell everybody about it! So that you can get amazing food too! But more because when a restaurant is terrible and services terrible you get a heads up and get to decide if you want to take a chance or not. Also there are so many experiences that we've had in our travels is always nice to have a voice I tell a good things and bad from a hotel experience to an adventure park... Thanks for making all of our opinions count!

Am able to pass on info to help other people to the good. If things good or bad will let them know. Pics always help so a good few of mine on there. App a good aid when looking for where to go, hotels, thíngs to do, good for disabled etc. Used every time I go away to look at place we're staying, reviews etc. A great help in general. Sis in law looks at the bad reviews, I look at the good. We find out what's good and bad therefore the hotels worth going to. Used Trip Advisor for long time now.

This is a senior high ranking and wonderful app , trip advisor is made available which is beneficial. It also indicates the premium features and the free ones.U can find locations using maps which is more easier, this app have been helpful to me for 6 months now . This is a fast ,secure, adorable and wonderful resource you'll should give it a try you won't let go.

I use this all the time when we travel. It is easy to use and I can tell from the reviews whether it's someplace we might enjoy or not. We just used it to find the nicest little place to eat in Cortez Colorado that I would never have known about otherwise.

We booked our excursion through *Picotourist in Costa Rica. 🇨🇷 * We had a great time on this tour at (Manuel Antonio National Park) Our Guide Luis Alonso, was knowledgeable,professional about all the nature activity in the park, up in the trees. Along our walk on the trail, Luis pointed out sloths,Monkeys, bats up in the trees & had us get a closer look through his Monocular & he also gives you info on each species. After the tour,you get to spend time on a beautiful beach.

I have used TripAdvisor almost exclusively for trips and activities everywhere. We love being able to skip the lines when we purchase tickets for the places we want to see and to experience cultural activities and tours.
TripAdvisor has always been a place I look for reviews when I want to see what would be worthwhile when I travel. I think I will like this feature of adding plans to each day in one saved place.

Making our upcoming anniversary / vacation a breeze!!!! Everything is in 1 place!!! I really love that, after spending 5hrs on my tablet, everything I looked at as something interesting to do and eat is all in 1 spot. When we arrive at our destination, we have a game plan of places to go / eat. It's like I have a travel agent at my fingertips, yes, I'm THAT old, 57, when you would hire people / companies to do this for you!!! Thanks TripAdvisor ❤️

Tripadvisor was my go to travel app. However, since the update, I can no longer sort hotels by traveler rating or by distance. The buttons exist but when I press apply, nothing changes. Interesting that when I deleted and reinstalled the app, the functionality returned?!?

I use this app often and find it very helpful. I typically use it to find reviews/recommendations about various hotels and restaurants in an area I am visiting, and sometimes I use it for suggesting different things to do in an area I am visiting such as electric bike rentals, parks, bike paths , farmers markets, etc. 😊

### 🌟 Excellent Travel Recommendations from Play Store! 🌟 I recently explored the Play Store and was thoroughly impressed by their travel recommendations for travelers! 📱✈️ Not only do they offer a wide range of apps and games, but their travel section is incredibly helpful. From apps that help you plan your itinerary to those that offer local insights and tips, the Play Store.

This app is incredibly helpful for when I'm planning my travel. All of the recommended activities I've booked through here have been excellent. It's intuitive and easy to use to not only book experiences, but to leave reviews.

Can no longer imagine a trip without referring to TripAdvisor We did lots of trips, just because we used the TripAdvisor and are immensely benefited by people who painstakingly write reviews here. I just love this app

Fantastic app. The only problem is that I have been a reviewer for TripAdvisor for some years now. But when I changed my phone I lost everything and have had to start all over again. Which I am not happy about. I was know on the app as Alans

TripAdvisor is an absolute game-changer for travelers and foodies alike. With its comprehensive database of reviews, photos, and recommendations, it's like having a personal tour guide in your pocket. Whether you're planning a vacation, looking for a new restaurant to try, or seeking insider tips on local attractions, TripAdvisor has got you covered. One of the best features of TripAdvisor is its user-generated content. Instead of relying on paid advertisements or sponsored listings.

Good App to use, only issue I found is when I get an email saying that someone asked a question in relation to a review I left, when I click the button/box in the email to review the said question, it opens the App, however does not take me directly to the question. As for the rest, no complaints.

l've been a guest reviewer for many years,l only give honest feedback as l find it, l give praise where it's due and hope to see the same when l review others feedback. l check out all of my holiday destinations abroad on TripAdvisor and rely on the wonderful service it offers. Really well done TripAdvisor. I often feel,we can be quick to complain but not so quick to praise. I hope l do that on Tripadvisor and hope it helps my fellow travellers as they help me. TripAdvisor is go to.

Have used TripAdvisor many times over the years to find hotels and activities for holidays. Been to some really fun places. Never been disappointed with what's been recommend. Especially loved Canyoning in Como!
Super easy to use, for both posting and finding reviews, really helpful and informative for trip planning.
One of the premier applications for travel, it allows users to effortlessly book tours, hotels, and all necessary arrangements for their journeys.

Find all the hidden gems in every zip code like a local. Trip Advisor always knocks it out of the park when I plan anything and everything related to my visited ShangriLa. Where are you going? Like having a private concierge in your hip pocket. Smile
Great app/site. Easy to use. Reviews are helpful. Excellent way of keeping track of where you've been so you can revisit the places you love.
I've used TripAdvisor for years when I travel. I use it now to explore where I now live! As a (now retired) server, I've used this app for tourists to give suggestions for exploring.

Gemination Eatery and Bar is a must-visit spot in Da Lat. It features a cozy and stylish atmosphere. I’m impressed with the unique cocktails they offer. The ambiance is both relaxed and sophisticated, making it an ideal choice for unwinding.
Always used this app for ideas and places to explore and forums to find out what the locals suggest... highly recommended! Going to use it for upcoming trip.
This is a great app for researching venues of interest. I use it for restaurants, holiday resorts, and hotels. I trust that the reviews are authentic and reliable.

I love putting reviews on the app, I hope it helps people to see what places are really like. I will always try and be fair to the people involved, i like it when they respond to what I have put, it is good to see that venues read what people are saying and taking the trouble to respond.

I really want to thank you for your help.thanks to the tripadvisor it has really make me to improve my business,I have become famous in my country because of this app .my business is doing very great in each and every day.thanks again and again to the tripadvisor I really appreciate your good job keep it up.

we had a great experience on the 2D/1N inca trail!! our guides Mike and Peter went above and beyond to make sure we were taken care of. the food made by the chefs was amazing! the drivers and porters took care of us and our belongings from start to finish. cannot recommend enough!!
Brilliant to see what genuine travellers think of various places worldwide. We have found so many places that we would never have experienced without Trip Adviser.

I always go to trip advisor to see what is new or happening in area I'm choosing to go to. This time it happened to be at our favorite get away spot Best Western on the Beach as it's not far from home it is a clean and friendly place to stay. The front desk staff is very helpful answering our questions or finding an answer for us

Awesome! TripAdvisor lets you save trips, create an itinerary and add saved favorites to specific days/times, and has the most reliable and comprehensive set of activities to learn about and choose from for any location in the states or around the world. I've returned to this app again and again to reap its benefits. Access to knowledgeable tourguides and thorough descriptions with user ratings all makes this worth it.

It is my pleasure to use this app.. to find a ways and very easy to searching somewhat. For looking! A tripAdvisor. Is very appreciating. Greatest most of all. Easy to find. A nice location. Restaurant many places you want to visit. And i like to plan. For booking and to travel at any places to visit.. TripAdvisor is a must.. and help us.
Great app to find and book activities while traveling. No issues communicating with the service providers through the app's chat feature. Useful for reviews as well.

Our go to site for dining out and where to stay. The public reviews are an enormous influence on where we stay and eat. Highly recommend this app for anyone who is looking to go dining or hotel hopping.
I love to write reviews to help others find great places that we have visited, as well as some places that were not so great. I think it's important to share our experiences.

Have used for many years now, checking out the latest reviews on hotels, restaurants, places etc both home & away. Bearing in mind what suits 1 traveller may not suit another. Generally the most trusted place for all reviews.
I always go to Trip Advisor for travel tips and reviews because I trust the opinions of other travelers. It is so very helpful!
A wonderful, interactive app to help you choose according to your individual requirements, and in turn, review your own experience.
I used trip advisor to take several side tours while vacationing in Italy. The ability to one-stop shop tours for several different cities was a godsend
After all these years, this app keeps getting better. It has rarely steered me wrong and has taken me to places I have never been to great delight. 2024 I still go to this app for great insight.

Had a lovely experience the food was really nice and specially the customer service is very good. The customer assistant farwa was very professional and nice to the customers. Overall highly recommended.thanks farwa

TripAdvisor provides excellent information that makes holidays and mini breaks more enjoyable! Great for Accommodation, Restaurants and Things to Do! Thank you! 🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟 The App continues (2024) to provide a great service to travellers seeking a bed, food or activities! 💗
Easy to access and read personal accounts. Like the pictures. I love this is travelers first hand experiences. I can usually find tidbits that make my decision making easier.
I found a 5 star hotel with your app, that I couldn't find on any other app. Also I didn't have any problems changing a credit card, it was so easy. love love this app Thank you!
I use this app for all of my officials and unofficial travels. It's great for almost everything. Where to eat, what to do, how to relax. This app is easy to use and very accurate.
Love it! Very helpful when looking for hotels, restaurants & even places to visit while traveling.
Over the years, I greatly benefitted from Tripadvisor. In retribution, I feel the need to provide info about personal experiences, with honest reviews that might help others.

The Trip Advisor app always works well and is great experience!The Trip Advisor app is fun to use,is very helpful with accurate info!Trip Advisor always works like it should! It's always a pleasure to suggest,advise and share information with others that would be helpful.They post info quickly to help others make good,educated choices!The pictures posted always look crisp! Thanks Trip Advisor! Wayne Salvatti

User friendly and easy to access for vast options to search reviews. I have been an avid traveler and reviewer for past 15 years. Love to research on TripAdvisor before making any trip for up to date information. Disappointed in that most of my reviews photos are posted upside down. No effort to correct it. I keep getting excuses. Very unprofessional service.

This is my go-to app when I'm planning any trip! Love how you can see all the hotel deals from different options and choose the lowest price available. I can find restaurants and attractions too and easily save every trip!!

The best teacher is experience. The best experience is someone else's. Honest, accurate, authentic, accountable. There used to be (many years ago) a practice of not publishing horrible experiences. No longer when found that these could have saved lives, as well as money and memories. I appreciate that the rated get to respond to their raters and fix the problem for a win-win.

I recently did a Sky Dive at the Black Knights Parachute Club near Lancaster. Being 85 years of age could have made the experience a little more testing. I have to say that the day went perfectly in every way. The staff are first class and made the day very memorable from first to last. Special thanks to Deano, my instructor and Alan the aerial and ground photographer. Thanks to everyone involved for making the day perfect in every way.
We look to Trip Advisor before traveling for info on places to stay, restaurants, and activities. Thank you to all that post their reviews.
A great App. We always check trip advisors for reviews when booking hotels. I leave reviews for other customers about our own experience.
The app is very useful in providing info on things to do, restaurants and accommodation and reviews from travelers.
I'd like to have the option to give halv stars as well. The app is a must, sometimes is very slow
It's a great app to leave reviews on different places you've been to and see what others have to say about places before booking yourself

This a great walking tour & excellent value for money. Our guide David was extremely knowledgeable, took us at a nice pace, stood in the shade each time he stopped to inform us on various sites, which was very important on a day where the temperature was 31°C. He had tickets to each place organised in advance so it was smooth & seamless with no delays. I could not recommend David & this particular tour highly enough. We took it on our first day in Porto & it really set us up to enjoy the city.

I had an incredible Jaipur trip with Aryavrit! The tour was well-organized, and our guide was knowledgeable and friendly, making the experience memorable. We visited iconic sites like Amber Fort and Hawa Mahal, and the insights provided were fascinating. Aryavrit made sure we were comfortable throughout the journey, and the attention to detail was impressive. Highly recommend Aryavrit for an authentic Jaipur experience!
Very good for finding things to do and places to eat, based on other peoples experiences

I purchased a 200k account and passed very quickly. I got the account as well within 2 minutes and made profit too. My payout was processed in less than 20 minutes, so they did really keep their promise. Customer support agents and support team is always there to assist. Highly recommended.

Trip Advisor easy and efficient resource to plan and complete in local experiences and activities before, and sometimes (if choice has seats still available) even the day before desire to do. Like that link to contact providing company clear up to departure, if have questions or changes need to be made

Arrived at lunchtime and the crowd outside was quite off-putting, but at lunch from $5.99, it's not surprising this place is popular. The girl on the front informed us of a 20 minute wait and she wasn't wrong. Everything went like clockwork and I couldn't fault any of the staff. Our waiter was extreme busy with his allotted tables but still made the point of saying hello and he would be with us shortly. When he arrived back, he brought 2 glasses of water which was unexpected but necessary.

I love being able to search for nearby restaurants and attractions when we are on the road. We've found many hidden gems thanks to this app. I also never go on a trip without checking things out first to find the best place to stay, things to do and places to eat.

Invariably useful when seeking places to stay or eat. There will always be mixed reviews of places, including some that can't be trusted, but you get used to building up a good picture of an establishment and it's rarely wrong.

Today, I had the privilege of visiting a historical place with Mr. Tas, and it was an unforgettable experience. Seeing such a wonderful place, I couldn't hold back my tears of joy. Having read numerous historical books and visited many countries, this particular place completely blew my mind. I want to express a big thank you for the detailed explanation provided. I will definitely come back again with my entire household. Thank you so much.

Seabreeze Adventures. Whale watching by zodiack. Excellent hot day in July. Four us were on this whale watch tour with 3 other small groups. The young lady in charge of saftey & guiding was excellent. She was excited as the passengers. Brorwyn is her name. I opologize if spelling is wrong. It was an exhillerating crossing, pounding through the choppy water. The skipper( Elliot ), took us to experience the Stellar sea lions first. That was exciting to see how huge they are. Whales! Yes:).

John from Majestic Tours together with the driver Mohammed took me any partner Gail to Alexandria for a day trip from Cairo.We visited the Library of Alexandria which was fascinating and also the Greco Roman Catacombs and the Fortress built on the site if the Pharos Lighthouse.John is very friendly and knowledgeable and the lunch at Antheos Restaurant overlooking the Mediterranean was also special.A great day out I would recommend this guide.Howard.

We have been traveling and using Trip Advisor for 13 years now and they have never let us down as long as you take the time to read the whole report and all the reviews and then interpret the information. There have been some reviews I have read and just got the impression the person was either a jerk or just having a bad day when they wrote the review and the opposite is true for the other way so read the whole review and then make your own judgement.

The reviews give a fair idea of the place and guidance to visit most of the tourist locations on the globe.The views of tourists and the ratings given help a traveller to makes his choice better.Reviews by frequent travellers save time to make a choice.
Easy to follow when writing a review+very useful when searching for new places to eat
Best platform to leave the feedback about the service and attractions. Thankyo for providing platform to share our opinion .
Excellent meal, great service. Thank you food was fantastic
Trip advisor is a non biased forum that allows you to be as truthful as you can be when reviewing hotels restaurants ect.
The app is great for finding local places to eat and stay, that you can trust. Very easy to use and great when on holiday for planning.
Very easy to use, brilliant way to select places to stay in Melbourne.
Senior.. has used TripAdvisor for many years on my world travels. Can always trust the advice and recommendations.. Will continue to share my experience. Happy Vactions Gordon (Cheshire UK 🇬🇧)
As a solo traveler, I greatly appreciate all the recommendations for most cities in the world! I know that if a tour or place is highly rated on Trip Advisor, then it's going to be good!
I always go to TripAdvisor to check reviews before I book hotels. I also always use it to see reviews of restaurants and attractions.
It is simple to use and great for planning trips or just seeing what others have to say about different hotels and activities or what the best dishes are in a restaurant.
Has not stirred me wrong yet. Food is always good. I have done tours with them too and every thing was Soo easy and paid for.
Useful however it is constantly it's asking for updates Very good and an essential for the smart traveler 😁🤠
We always check Trip Advisor whether in town or on vacation. The decision where to eat or stay is always a direct result of Trip Advisor information.
TripAdvisor app is always my first check of local places to eat, sleep and stuff to do without exception. In all the years I've used it, it's never let me down.
Very easy to navigate and use, and helpful to find places to visit and travel to
Seems easy to work your way round the app and easier than having to keep signing in all the time
I used the app during my last travel to Barcelona. Was very helpful and helped me to do many show and attractions reservation.

Great place to get other people's thoughts on places. Helps me decide if i should visit or not. As everyone's experiences are different, I tend to make my decision based on the majority of either positive or negative reviews
Great Planning App Very easy to flag Things to Do in cities we're visiting, and then map them so we can cluster activities together
Great for looking at reviews for booking. Very useful for checking out hotels worldwide. Highly recommended
Tripadvisor is the perfect way to plan out a vacation, or plan a date night.
Very good app when you're looking for places to eat, see, ... a must have travel partner
Very user friendly and gives authentic information regarding trips.
I used this all the time! Location, pictures and reviews, hours and phone # and gps address and can book overnight stay.
As a Celiac I rely on Trip Advisor to help me choose for holidays, short breaks or meals out
Easy and simply aap most important to find new city and activities I love this app, it really helpful for my business too
Great app, right place to get everything you need before your destination arrival.
Lovely place to eat. Staff were friendly. Food lovely + plentiful. Would recommend.
Easy to use. Safe to purchase tours. We have used it in Italy, France, Belgium, Luxembourg and the Netherlands.
Awesome for finding great places to eat when you visit new places.
Love live TripAdvisor. Always has all I need to complete my trip planning.
Amazing trip, tour and hotel planner. Have never been disappointed 👌👌👌
I Always check the app before making a decision of a place to visit or to go eat, I get best ideas and detailed information.
Brilliant stay recommend to family's with children food very high standard to choice need more curry's
Great place to look for activities, lodging and places to eat.
Very helpful, especially if you're exploring & discovering
Good place to gain foreknowledge of venues and also to leave a description of your experiences.
Easy to use, good interface. No bugs so far.

We had a lovely stay at the Carlton, it's my favourite place. Incredible Sea views, amazing service, a special shout out to Ben, thoroughly enjoyed breakfast. I slept really well. I didn't use the pool, but it was lovely to see people enjoying it. I am looking forward to my next visit.
Very easy to use and understand, sharing comment enjoyable

Couldn't plan my holidays without Trip Advisor, especially the restaurant reviews, which I rely on. The way it will tell you what's near you now is very helpful when in an unknown town, exploring. Plus it's linked to Google maps so will then take you there! Also the Filters are very helpful. I use them to search for gluten free menus.

I've been using Tripadvisor I must say, it's truly outstanding. The performance is flawless – it's fast, responsive, and incredibly reliable. I've never experienced any crashes or slowdowns, even when multitasking or using it for extended periods. The user interface is intuitive and well-designed, making navigation a breeze. Whether I'm accessing features or customizing settings, everything is neatly organized and easy to find. Plus, the app's sleek design adds to the

Good: There's number of things you can do within this app! Book hotels, flights, check out restaurants or sightseeing spots, download offline guides to the city you're visiting, there's an integration with Uber, so when you find a anything you want to visit, you can right away call a taxi there. Just perfect, must have for all travellers!

Love doing reviews and sharing my experiences good and bad with others. We have travelled by car, plane and ferry stopping off all over the UK, Ireland and abroad. Reading reviews before we go really helps us plan our trips. I read the Excellent, very good and average and also take time to read tge poor and terrible there's always something useful in most people's experience.

Great app. Works well. Good for comparing prices. Great for seeing people's photos of places other than just the ones used for 'selling' it. Take reviews as a guide rather than 100% accurate. TripAdvisor is perfect example of too many people with too much time on their hands. Quick to complain but wouldn't think to review having experienced the opposite. Great site for guidance however keeping in mind it is mainly personal preference apposed to complete accuracy.

Have been utilising the app to plan and have posted over 100 review. Love the app. Be it in India or International including 69 countries I have travelled over the last 50 years, have found the trip advisor app useful.

Super app vey interesting so very Happy Works as advertised. I am using the free version for now. My only wishes are about speed: that it loads faster, and that email notifications for new posts came right away (I get them delayed by almost one hour), but it's pretty good for a free tool. Very easy to install and set up.

I'm using TripAdvisor on all my appliances and I've been pleased with the service and functuality of it. This app does not make any difference in that. Sometimes you can even find a lower priced hotel offers here. An every day tool while travelling or planning to travel. One can easily find new places worth visiting. I will warmly recommend it.

I don't go anywhere without checking TripAdvisor first! Love this app, especially for restaurants and hotels. I always go straight for the traveller photos to see what a hotel place really looks like as the 'management photos' are often enhanced/photoshopped so I love seeing through the eyes of the average traveller to see what you're really getting... Though when people post photos of themselves/family I find that quite annoying, I want to see the place not your face! 😂

By far the experience is good with lots of information. Overall amazing experience with the app but the only thing is the points which we get after reviewing any place. There should be something done either discounts or reimbursement in terms of money so that we will be motivated to review more by some way. Right now badges have no meaning.

Have to be honest, I use trip advisor reviews before I book any hotel to get a clearer picture of the facilities and food available. I also make sure to leave my own reviews too so I can help my fellow travellers. It's also one of the best online resources for finding local things to do when away and booking them cheaper than at the hotel. I highly recommend it.

What has happened. Since the last update it has changed my name back to an old one I used to use and it has lost over 300 odd reviews I have done and all my saves. Not impressed at all! 29 July 2021 - update - helpdesk was really helpful. Took a bit of time to sort out but all my 365 reviews are back. Hooray😀

content: Super easy to use and great for recommendations and tracking plans.
Too many times you just take a chance trying a place out. Its great to see people's opinion of a place before goin
Great ideas for visiting different places and finding different places to eat and drink
Fantastic as always. Great place for a special lunch or a quick bit Dario again looked after us. Grazie team Volare

This has got to be my favourite App never book a holiday without checking here first, I'm not always persuded by the reviews I booked a holiday once read the reviews afterwards and was horrified by some of the negatives,turned out to be the best holiday I've ever had. This App is so easy to use,you can find great hotels ect at great prices ask questions on member boards post and look at photos hotel staff and people who've stayed there. It's part of the excitement when I'm on my holiday countdown

I find that this app really fills the void of others. I like it because I can find tours, hotel transfers, accurate foodie reviews plus, wait for it, bloggers who will meet you and take you on a particular tour. And there are people in every country who do this. They may be pricier than "Hop on- hop off" buses, but you will see unique parts of whatever city you are in!

To anyone planning a trip, this app is a must because however much you plan there might be something you don't know is there and could miss it. So by using the app your trip will be enhanced. Sadly and this is a warning to everyone including myself, check before you go. I wish I had before I booked the table because the experience was not up to our expectations.
TripAdvisor is the only company that tells the truth about all hotels, if it was not there it would have been difficult to know the real place

I use TripAdvisor regularly to source decent places to eat when away from home and it mostly gives good advice. I've learned to look for a particular profile, with mostly excellent, tailing down through very good and good. Those that have very variable ratings with too many at the bottom often disappoint.
Great app. Works well and loads of offers
Great app to assist in getting local knowledge or leaving honest reviews. I try to drop a review everytime I go somewhere new..
This app has proven itself time and time again when looking for places to eat at foreign locations.
Works well to leave reviews and see what others think. Helpful when planning a visit to an unfamiliar location.
Brilliant App really helped planning vacation especially restaurants and things to do. Logical accurate app.
Great App to look for restaurant, hotels, reviews, plan a trip, search for places, make bookings, etc.
Great App it's the most trusted app for the travellers in any mode.Travel and share your experiences Awesome
Great app to find top rated hotels, restaurants and trips anywhere anytime.
Great app. Most of all, when you get hints about places that you have not visited.
A Very good application to offer you a very good thought for a place to go or eat !!!
Very easy to use and helpful for other travellers to review hotels and such
Great app. I use the app mainly to read reviews and find exciting places to visit while on vacation.
Works perfectly for what I need in terms of looking up places, reviews and posting reviews.
I never go anywhere without having a look at the reviews. When I post reviews, I try to include as much detail as possible to help inform other visitors
Very helpful in getting guidance on traveling to new locations.
Always the first app I go to when planning our travels,, easy to use & full of great helpfull reviews 👍 👌
,Nice good advice helpful. Would use it on a business trip or a visit or a family trip to under water world or maybe some where else who know life's what you make it.
In my opinion, the only trustworthy app to find out the truth about something, anything, is worth the time to pursue.
Helps a lot other travellers to have an idea about,hotels , areas etc
First port of call when looking for accommodation, places to eat and attractions.
